  "text": "Effect of heterogeneity of vertex degree and community size. To study the effect of heterogeneity of vertex degrees and community sizes on Quasi-Surprise, we further apply various methods to a type of classical modular network, Lancichinetti-Fortunato-Rachicchi (LFR) networks [CITATION_1] ( Fig. 1C) , which are able to mimic the general properties of many real-world networks, such as the community structures, the heterogeneity of vertex degrees and community sizes.",
